---
import Layout from "~/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Newsletter"
  description="The Undoverfit newsletter is coming. In the meantime, the RSS feed has everything."
>
  <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-prose px-5">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl">Newsletter</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-muted-light dark:text-muted-dark">
      I am still figuring out the right way to send these without leaning on
      a service that tracks readers. Until I have something I'm happy with,
      the calmest way to follow along is the <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-muted-light dark:text-muted-dark">
      If you would rather be pinged personally when the email version is
      live, write me at
      <a
        href="mailto:vadale93@gmail.com?subject=undoverfit%20newsletter"
        >vadale93@gmail.com</a
      >
      with the subject line "undoverfit newsletter" and I will put you on a
      short manual list.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
